pullsbody:
Not entirely sure how well this works on uwsgi or gunicorn, but I think it should be safe... everything being added is just things that help to find the "geodude" module if the environment can't by itself.

This makes it possible to run this in a virtualenv using Apache/mod_wsgi.
pull_repo_desc: Geolocation via IP address using Maxmind location databases.
pull_commit_message:
make service.wsgi work with mod_wsgi

Not entirely sure how well this works on uwsgi or gunicorn, but I think it should be safe... everything being added is just things that help to find the "geodude" module if the environment can't by itself.

This makes it possible to run this in a virtualenv using Apache/mod_wsgi.
